ding <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἀρῆς</foreign> for <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἄρης.</foreign> (Cf. <tns opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tns\">pf.</tns> <mood opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"mood\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ part.\">part.</a></mood> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ᾱ)ρημένος</foreign> <xr opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"xr\"> <lbl opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"lbl\">=</lbl> <ref targOrder=\"U\" lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"ref\">βεβλαμμένος</ref></xr>, and pr. n. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Ἄρης</foreign> (cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0654.tlg002:20\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Corn.</author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">ND</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">20</biblScope> </bibl>), perh. also <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἄρος, ἀρειά, ἐπήρεια</foreign>; perh. an old <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">ē</tr_> stem.)</sense> </entryFree>"}]}